Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.

Trim the @Carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into
pieces about 1/2 cm thick.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and carrot. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a
splash of @water{splash}, then cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and allow to
cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove the veg and place in a #medium bowl{}. Cover to keep warm.

Wipe out your frying pan, then pop back on frying pan on medium-high heat with
a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} to the pan and use a
#spoon{} to mash into a mince-like texture as it cooks.

Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Once the veggie mince is cooked, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @Hoisin Sauce{64%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Simmer the sauce until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @Udon Noodles{220%g} to the pan along with the broccoli and carrot.

Toss to coat in the sauce, using a #fork{} to gently separate them. Simmer
until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of
@water{splash} if the sauce is too thick.

Share the noodles between your #serving bowls{}. Enjoy!